ight: 26px; margin: 0;">Credibility of storyteller to the target audience</=
p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-right=
: 0; margin-top: 3.75px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1=
a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Confirmatory updates=
</p></li><li style=3D"margin-bottom: 3.75px; margin-left: 7.5px; margin-rig=
ht: 0; margin-top: 3.75px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: =
#1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">Persistence of sto=
ries over time</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The best thing for a company or projec=
t&#8217;s narrative is to have a lot of people with credibility to the targ=
et audience tell stories with roughly similar positive themes again and aga=
in over a long period of time, with new examples of the same positive theme=
s added in. The more authentic and the less coordinated it all seems, the b=
etter.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">It&#8217;s hard to pull off, particularly because =
so much of it needs to be organic, seeded with just the right amount of dir=
ection from the company or team and its core supporters. When it works, tho=
ugh, it&#8217;s a powerful thing, the benefits of which compound over time.=
&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;">Benefits compound because <strong>narratives are Lindy</=
strong>. The longer people believe something about a company, the longer th=
ey&#8217;re likely to believe something about that company.&nbsp;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0=
;">A great current example is <strong>Apple vs. Facebook</strong>.&nbsp;</p=
><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 1em 0;">The narrative around Apple is that it&#8217;s a world-class desig=
n-and-privacy-first company whose products say something good about the peo=
ple who own them. That narrative began, very intentionally, under Steve Job=
s, and it carries through to today. It&#8217;s armor. Anything that doesn&#=
8217;t fit the narrative practically bounces right off; anything that feeds=
 the narrative gets added.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Claims that the App Store&#8217;s 30=
% take is anti-competitive have barely grazed the company. Apple&#8217;s re=
cent decision to put <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkUuOwy=
AMhk9TdkRAyGvBYjZzjYiASVEJICCtcvtx28VIyA8Z-7c-G91gT-VSOdVG3mZtVwYV4VUDtAaFn=
BXK6q3io5j7QS7EKmn5PMzE19UVgEP7oFo5geRzC97o5lP8dDAmBnJXTnPoDcA4wGAFX_pxm9js=
nHY407j5q6tP6yEaUPCEcqUIJKh7a7ne-p-b-MX3er06cK5LZcfMAuTg46NiLJjg6NiMRuccoNI=
